I've tried doing it in the deploy function (but get an invalid argument count error, so the deploy function checks the constructor). And, doing something like ```      const [owner, addr1] = await ethers.getSigners();
params = { from: owner,to: addr1, value: ethers.utils.parseUnits(strEther, "ether").toHexString()};
      const txHash = await owner.provider.sendTransaction(params);
``` results in ```Error: invalid hexlify value (argument="value", value={"from":"<SignerWithAddress 0xf39Fd6e51aad88F6F4ce6aB8827279cffFb92266>","to":"<SignerWithAddress 0x70997970C51812dc3A010C7d01b50e0d17dc79C8>","value":"0x1bc16d674ec80000"}, code=INVALID_ARGUMENT, version=bytes/5.4.0)```
